# Interview Preparation — Full-Stack (Angular + Java/Spring)

A curated, **deeply explained** interview Q&A set tailored to a frontend engineer
(5+ yrs Angular 8→19, TypeScript, RxJS, NgRx) who is now learning backend
(Java 17, Spring Boot, JPA/Hibernate, SQL).

Each file is standalone. Questions are ordered roughly **fundamentals → advanced**,
and most include a short **"Why interviewers ask"** note plus a **practical code example**.

## Files

| # | File | Topic |
|---|------|-------|
| 1 | [01-angular.md](01-angular.md) | Angular (v9 → v19): components, DI, RxJS, signals, change detection, routing, forms, NgRx, performance, micro-frontends, testing, migration |
| 2 | [02-javascript-typescript.md](02-javascript-typescript.md) | JavaScript core (closures, event loop, prototypes, `this`) + TypeScript (types, generics, utility types, decorators) |
| 3 | [03-html-css.md](03-html-css.md) | HTML5 semantics, accessibility, CSS box model, flexbox, grid, specificity, responsive design, SCSS |
